Tim Krul congratulated Sunderland striker Jermain Defoe on his goal at half-time of the Wear-Tyne derby . 
  Sportsmail's Jamie Carragher criticised Krul for his actions . 
  The Newcastle goalkeeper appeared to congratulate Defoe after the goal . 
  Carragher says he has nothing against Krul but he should not have congratulated Defoe . 
  Andrew Flintoff and Gary Neville also criticised the Newcastle keeper . 
 